intro.description: From Electrical Engineering to Full-Stack Web Development, I bring a unique skill set and passion for learning to every project.

about.statement: From electrical engineering to full-stack web development, I bring a unique skill set and passion for learning to every project.
about.summary: I am an experienced Electrical Engineer and Full-Stack Web Developer with a passion for continuous learning and improving my skills to build bigger, faster, and better. Offering expertise in designing motor control centers, VFDs, control and instrumentation, and power transmission systems with a focus around hydropower and other renewables, as well as front-end and back-end web development, cybersecurity risk management, IT, and server administration. Always staying up-to-date with the latest technologies and constantly expanding skills to deliver efficient and effective solutions to complex problems.
description: I am a versatile engineer and web developer with a passion for learning and problem-solving. With a degree in electrical engineering and five years of experience designing motor control, VFDs, control and instrumentation, and power transmission systems, I have a solid foundation in engineering principles and technical expertise.

In my free time, I taught myself a variety of programming languages and quickly applied these skills to secure a remote job during the pandemic lockdowns. Over the past three years, my role has expanded to include front-end development, back-end development, cybersecurity risk management, and even handling administrative tasks on Microsoft Azure and Microsoft Admin 365.

My portfolio showcases my proficiency in a broad range of front-end and full-stack web development technologies, including React, Vue, MongoDB, Mongoose, NodeJS, ExpressJS, Apache, MySQL, Wordpress, PHP, Codeigniter, HTML5, CSS3, and C#. I also have experience in cybersecurity risk management, including vulnerability assessments, penetration testing, threat analysis, and security awareness training.

Whether it's designing complex electrical systems, building user-friendly web applications, or ensuring the security and integrity of digital systems, I take pride in delivering high-quality work that meets the needs of my clients. I am excited to bring my diverse skill set and experience to a new position and tackle new challenges.
description1: I am a versatile engineer and web developer with a passion for learning and problem-solving. With a degree in electrical engineering and five years of experience designing motor control, VFDs, control and instrumentation, and power transmission systems, I have a solid foundation in engineering principles and technical expertise. During my five years in the field, I gained an appreciation for design work more broadly, and I found myself drawn to the world of programming and began to explore and teach myself a variety of languages in my free time, first as a hobby, but eventually leading me to pursue a career in web development.

When the pandemic and subsequent lockdowns caused most engineering projects to be either halted or cancelled and engineering positions were scarce, I leveraged my newly acquired skills and found a remote job that allowed me to continue developing my programming abilities.

Over the last three years, my skillset has grown from front-end design using Wordpress, PHP, Codeigniter, HTML5, CSS3, and some C# to a full-stack designer with proficiency in React, Vue, MongoDB, Mongoose, NodeJS, ExpressJS, Apache, MySQL, and others. I have also taken on additional responsibilities in cybersecurity risk management and administrative tasks on Microsoft Azure and Microsoft Admin 365, further expanding my expertise.

As a continuous learner, I always stay up-to-date with the latest technologies and strive to deliver efficient and effective solutions to complex problems. Whether it's designing electrical systems or developing web applications, my goal is to use my skills and expertise to create innovative and impactful solutions.

projects.title: UK Crime Reports Dashboard
projects.description: A dashboard built in React making use of the UK Crime API. You can search for crime reports in the UK using a variety of options: Selecting a police force jurisdiction, a neighborhood or list of neighborhoods, or by choosing specific coordinates or area using Mapbox. All results are displayed in a custom-built datatable, and can be downloaded as JSON or CSV. If the results received from the API contain location data, you can also view them in a map rendering where those reports occurred.
